        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 16:40:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs there a plan to put all the charts as subcharts so that there is only one Helm chart",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "060cc2ce4dc7a8aa3824a5d3182cf9f5c2baa834",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5033,
          "name": "Akhila Kishore",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "akhila.kishore@intel.com",
          "username": "akhilakishore"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 16:49:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhy do you have services for packetgen and firewall\nWhat is the purpose of the ingress in sink\nA: Actually they are included when I create a new helm chart using 'helm create'. Will remove them.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "181e696eebdb4fa6170cf0c29543aff6b6dd8acb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5033,
          "name": "Akhila Kishore",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "akhila.kishore@intel.com",
          "username": "akhilakishore"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 16:49:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs there a plan to put all the charts as subcharts so that there is only one Helm chart.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "5dda2c4c3f803a969875c93c2c08a5cb5b72aa6a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5033,
          "name": "Akhila Kishore",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "akhila.kishore@intel.com",
          "username": "akhilakishore"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 16:54:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs there a plan to put all the charts as subcharts so that there is only one Helm chart\nA: Yes the plan is to create a single helm chart to deploy vFirewall. But, when we create network CRDs that will alter network configuration and cause problems while creating subsequent ones. It is my understanding that we need to introduce delays while doing so. So the current plan of action is to have them run individually and then align them to have a single chart bring up all the pods.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "9d496666bf8b61fa308dbe227a2cee1d8d624283",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 285,
          "name": "Ritu Sood",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ritu.sood@intel.com",
          "username": "ritusood"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 16:58:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(4 comments)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "bdcbb68c867519a2318ba73c310f7076341ae2fb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 285,
          "name": "Ritu Sood",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ritu.sood@intel.com",
          "username": "ritusood"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 17:03:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Is there a plan to put all the charts as subcharts so that there is\n > only one Helm chart\n > A: Yes the plan is to create a single helm chart to deploy\n > vFirewall. But, when we create network CRDs that will alter network\n > configuration and cause problems while creating subsequent ones. It\n > is my understanding that we need to introduce delays while doing\n > so. So the current plan of action is to have them run individually\n > and then align them to have a single chart bring up all the pods.\n\nNot sure how having multiple charts solves that problem. The networks created are consumed in the same Helm chart.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1d3836b9aadbf6e646072c35c5fe97b14de8fbdb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5033,
          "name": "Akhila Kishore",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "akhila.kishore@intel.com",
          "username": "akhilakishore"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-15 17:11:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWell different chart consumes different network configuration right? https://github.com/onap/multicloud-k8s/blob/master/kud/tests/_functions.sh#L118  I am manually running the charts one after the only to introduce delay. And it is easy to debug. This is just inital assessment.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
